        {
            "id": "4449153",
            "title": "SA Asks: Would Trump's drug price cuts hurt biotech more than pharma?",
            "description": "<html><body><p dir=\"ltr\">Would the cost-cutting measures for U.S. prescription drugs <a href=\"https://www.whitehouse.gov/presidential-actions/2025/05/delivering-most-favored-nation-prescription-drug-pricing-to-american-patients/\" rel=\"nofollow\">proposed by the Trump administration</a> on Monday hurt the biotech sector more than pharma?</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">We asked Seeking Alpha analysts <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/author/stephen-ayers\">Stephen Ayers</a> and <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/author/edmund-ingham\">Edmund Ingham</a> for their views.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/author/stephen-ayers\">Stephen Ayers</a>: Pharmaceutical companies are more directly impacted by the proposed cuts, but they have the resources to withstand some pressure. The impact on biotechnology companies is more nuanced, but these changes will be reflected in valuations. If the pricing power is reduced across the board for drugs, a Phase 2 investigational drug’s net present value, or NPV, for example, would be lower than in the past, reducing the valuation of a biotechnology company. <strong> </strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/author/edmund-ingham\">Edmund Ingham</a>: Right now, the proposed cuts to drug prices have - somewhat bizarrely - brought buoyancy to biotech and pharma stocks - the biotech ETF (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NYSEARCA:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/XBI\" title=\"SPDR® S&amp;P Biotech ETF\">XBI</a></span>) gained &gt;4% on Monday, as did stock prices of most Big Pharma companies. <strong> </strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">This may reflect one of two things - firstly, that pharmas and biotechs are not taking the president seriously - after all, these same proposed policy changes were easily defeated in President Trump’s first term in office by the pharma industry. Secondly, the biotech sector is suffering, and has been for some time. Having hit rock bottom, perhaps the industry is prepared to welcome change of any kind.<strong> </strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/screeners/9409aededb-Top-Pharmaceuticals-Stocks\">Top Pharmaceuticals Stocks</a></li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/screeners/9409aededa-Top-Biotechnology-Stocks\">Top Biotechnology Stocks</a></li>\n</ul>\n</body></html>",
            "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2193741302/image_2193741302.jpg?io=getty-c-w750",
            "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/news/4449153-sa-asks-would-trumps-drug-price-cuts-hurt-biotech-more-than-pharma",
            "pub_date": "2025-05-16 04:46:15",
            "source": "seekalpha",
            "kind": 1,
            "language": "en"
